    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-09-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="290"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Loring</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-09-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 10, 1889</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 12.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department was glad to receive your No. 7, of
                    the 9th ultimo, touching the remission of the fine imposed on Captain Colcord,
                    of the American bark <hi rend="italic">Carrie Heckle</hi>, at Lourenço
                    Marques.</p>
                <p>In view of a letter from Messrs. A. Mudgett &amp; Co., of 39 South street, New
                    York, dated the 5th instant, I have to ask that you will kindly collect the
                    amount and remit the same to the above company through this Department.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
